<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-06T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="73" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/235: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-06T18:00:00+08:00">June 6, 1932—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 6—4:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>622. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">General McCoy</persName>
                            and the other members of the League Commission arrived here last night.
                            They expect to remain about 2 weeks before proceeding to Japan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>